> Phase 5 — the narrative report, rendered by `tar_quarto()` in `_targets.R` (run
> `targets::tar_make()` first so the target store exists). Governance:
> `.claude/policies/analysis/results-writing.md`, `reporting.md`, `figures.md`.

**Results are objective and dynamic.** Every number — and every data-dependent
word (rankings, "which beats which", directions) — is generated by inline code, so
the text updates itself when the data change. Tables use legible paper labels
(labels-first), estimates carry confidence intervals, and figures use
colorblind-safe palettes (Okabe-Ito / `ggsci`).

```{r}
#| label: read-target
doubled <- targets::tar_read(doubled)
```

The example value is `r doubled` (sourced from the pipeline, not typed by hand).

